4. IMPORT ISSUES
================================================================================

No import resolution failures. The library has 15 modules declared in
cabal's exposed-modules, all with matching source files. Import graph
is a DAG with no circular dependencies:

  Leaf modules (no project deps): Prelude, Types
  Mid-tier: XML, Config, Store, Object.Storage, Auth.Policy, Auth.SigV4
  Handlers: Bucket.Handler, Object.Handler, List.Handler, Multipart.Manager
  Top: Server, Multipart.Handler, Presigned

Build passes, so all imports resolve. However, there are unused import
warnings (see section 1) and one deprecated API usage (requestBody in
Server.hs line 171).

The deprecated `requestBody` call in Server.hs line 171 should be replaced
with `getRequestBodyChunk`. These have identical signatures:
  requestBody :: Request -> IO ByteString
  getRequestBodyChunk :: Request -> IO ByteString

